    <note type="biography">
        <p>Businessman. Only child of Godfrey Wedgwood and Mary Hawkshaw; his mother died of complications after his birth. Joined the Wedgwood pottery firm in 1882 after his father’s health broke down; became a partner in 1891; director, 1905. First mayor of Stoke-on-Trent, 1909–10. Served in the South African War and was killed serving in the First World War.</p></note>
